## 6. Signing and Distribution

### Self-Signed Certificate (Development/Free Distribution)

```bash
# Download ZXPSignCmd from Adobe-CEP/CEP-Resources
# Create self-signed certificate
./ZXPSignCmd -selfSignedCert US CA "Your Company" "Your Name" password123 certificate.p12

# Sign the extension
./ZXPSignCmd -sign ./dist ./YourExtension.zxp certificate.p12 password123 -tsa http://timestamp.digicert.com/
```

### 2024 Known Issue: Cross-Platform Signing

**Problem**: ZXP files signed on macOS may fail on Windows and vice versa.

**Workaround**: Sign on the target platform:
- Sign macOS versions on macOS
- Sign Windows versions on Windows

**Best Practices**:
```bash
# Before signing, clean up:
find ./dist -name ".DS_Store" -delete
find ./dist -name "__MACOSX" -type d -exec rm -rf {} +
find ./dist -type l -delete  # Remove symlinks
find ./dist -empty -delete   # Remove empty files
```

### ZXP Packaging Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# build-zxp.sh

VERSION="1.0.0"
EXTENSION_NAME="YourExtension"
CERT_FILE="certificate.p12"
CERT_PASS="your-password"
TSA="http://timestamp.digicert.com/"

# Clean build
rm -rf dist
npm run build

# Clean problematic files
find ./dist -name ".DS_Store" -delete
find ./dist -name "*.map" -delete

# Sign
./tools/ZXPSignCmd -sign ./dist "./${EXTENSION_NAME}_v${VERSION}.zxp" $CERT_FILE $CERT_PASS -tsa $TSA

# Verify
./tools/ZXPSignCmd -verify "./${EXTENSION_NAME}_v${VERSION}.zxp" -certInfo
```

### Installation Methods

1. **Adobe Exchange** (Recommended for distribution): Submit ZXP to [Adobe Exchange](https://exchange.adobe.com/)

2. **Anastasiy's Extension Manager**: Third-party tool for installing ZXP files

3. **Manual Installation**:
   - macOS: `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/CEP/extensions/`
   - Windows: `C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Roaming\Adobe\CEP\extensions\`

---

## 7. Version Compatibility

### CEP Version Matrix

| CEP Version | Premiere Pro Version | Chrome Version |
|-------------|---------------------|----------------|
| CEP 12      | 25.0+ (2025)        | Chromium 99    |
| CEP 11      | 22.0-24.x (2022-2024)| Chromium 88   |
| CEP 10      | 14.0-21.x (2020-2021)| Chromium 74   |
| CEP 9       | 13.x (2019)         | Chromium 61    |

### Multi-Version Support in Manifest

```xml
<ExecutionEnvironment>
    <HostList>
        <!-- Support Premiere Pro 2020 through 2025+ -->
        <Host Name="PPRO" Version="[14.0,99.9]"/>
    </HostList>
    <RequiredRuntimeList>
        <!-- Minimum CEP version required -->
        <RequiredRuntime Name="CSXS" Version="10.0"/>
    </RequiredRuntimeList>
</ExecutionEnvironment>
```

### Runtime Version Detection

```javascript
// js/main.js
const csInterface = new CSInterface();

function checkCompatibility() {
    const hostEnv = csInterface.hostEnvironment;
    const appVersion = parseFloat(hostEnv.appVersion);
    const cepVersion = hostEnv.CEPVersion;

    console.log(`Premiere Pro: ${appVersion}`);
    console.log(`CEP Version: ${cepVersion}`);

    // Feature detection
    if (appVersion >= 25.0) {
        // Premiere Pro 2025 features
        enableNewFeatures();
    } else if (appVersion >= 22.0) {
        // Premiere Pro 2022-2024 features
        enableLegacyMode();
    }

    return {
        pproVersion: appVersion,
        cepVersion: cepVersion,
        isSupported: appVersion >= 14.0
    };
}
```

### ExtendScript Version Handling

```javascript
// jsx/hostscript.jsx
MyExtension.compatibility = {

    getPProVersion: function() {
        return parseFloat(app.version);
    },

    hasFeature: function(featureName) {
        var version = this.getPProVersion();

        var featureMap = {
            'audioChannelMapping': version >= 13.0,
            'productionWorkflows': version >= 14.0,
            'essentialGraphics': version >= 12.0,
            'captionsAPI': version >= 15.0
        };

        return featureMap[featureName] || false;
    }
};
```

---

## Summary: Quick Start Checklist

1. **Choose Your Path**: UXP for new projects (future-proof), CEP for legacy support
2. **Use Bolt CEP**: Modern Vite-based toolchain with TypeScript support
3. **Structure Code**: Separate JS (panel), JSX (ExtendScript), and CSXS (config)
4. **Promise-Wrap evalScript**: Avoid callback hell with async/await pattern
5. **Enable Debug Mode**: Set PlayerDebugMode registry/defaults for development
6. **Test Cross-Platform**: Sign on target platforms due to 2024 signing issue
7. **Version Guard**: Check app version before using newer APIs

